Maradona spent five years at Argentinos Juniors, from 1976 to 1981, scoring 115 goals in 167 appearances before his US$ 4 million transfer to Boca Juniors.[30] Maradona received offers to join other clubs, including River Plate who offered to make him the club's best paid player.[31] Nevertheless, Maradona expressed his will to be transferred to Boca Juniors, the team he always wanted to play for.[32]
